<p class="p2">a series of collages to raise awareness of global issues like over consumption, body dismorphia and sustainability. my aim was to bring together found materials on a white background, in varied compositions to create a singular image. for example, one the pieces consists of an image of a worker ploughing a tea farm in rural china, layered on top is one of china's new, popular exports, a cheap plastic washing machine ball made from a factory. i wanted to create a conversation or challenge between the two ideas, old vs new, natural vs chemically engineered?</p>
